snippet.textDisplay:
I swear sometimes, It's like the people who get Ramsay to come and help them have NEVER seen an episode of Kitchen Nightmares, not even as research for what to expect when they know he's gonna show up. It's like,


"Alright, guys, Gordon and the camera crew are gonna be here by this time on Thursday. Should we maybe order a few fresh ingredients?"
"Nah, we've been using the same ingredients for 54 years, no reason to change now."
"Mkay, should we maybe have a look at cleaning out the moldy lemons and the rancid chicken in the walk-in?"
"Nah, I cornered a raccoon in there last night and I don't want to risk letting him out."
"Alright, sure."
